    <fr:title text="relations for program equivalence"><fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> for program equivalence</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e,e']]></fr:tex> be two programs of type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\tau ]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e']]></fr:tex> are <html:em><html:strong>observationally equivalent</html:strong></html:em> when for any other program <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  \tau  \to  {\mathopen {}\left (\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h{\mathopen {}\left (e\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> terminates if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h{\mathopen {}\left (e'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> terminates. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_\tau ]]></fr:tex> is the set of programs of type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\tau ]]></fr:tex>, observational equivalence therefore forms a <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_\tau \mathbin {\nrightarrow } E_\tau ]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
