                <fr:title text="relations in operational semantics"><fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> in operational semantics</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> represent the set of states in a machine; then the behavior of this machine is usually described by a pair of <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S \colon  E\mathbin {\nrightarrow } E]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V\colon  E\mathbin {\nrightarrow } {\mathopen {}\left \{\star \right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {S} e']]></fr:tex> when it is possible for the machine to transition from state <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e']]></fr:tex> and such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\mathrel {V} \star ]]></fr:tex> when the machine can halt in state <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
